    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nThe NeoVim crashes when continuously scrolling with \"j\" or \"k\" keys when the text is in Cyrillic.\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\nnvim --clean\r\nwrite text in Cyrillic\r\nscroll with \"j\" or \"k\" (continuously)\r\nneovim/src/nvim/grid.c:636: grid_put_linebuf: Assertion `0 <= row && row < grid->rows' failed.\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nNeoVim does not crash.\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nNVIM v0.10.0-dev-2195+gd4bd6b1ea Build type: RelWithDebInfo LuaJIT 2.1.1706185428\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nno\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nopenSUSE Tumbleweed\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nkitty 0.32.2\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\n256\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nFrom repo",
